  "commentary": "With SPX at 6812.1 sitting above the massive negative gamma wall at 6800 (-77.8B), dealers are currently forced to buy the market as it moves higher, creating mechanical bid support that amplifies upward momentum. The breakout regime combined with heavy negative GEX concentration between 6795-6815 means any pullback toward 6800 will trigger aggressive dealer buying, while a push above 6815 clears the negative gamma field and could accelerate moves toward the 6830 positive gamma ceiling where dealers flip to sellers.\n\nKey inflection point is 6800 - hold above and dealer buying supports further upside, break below and the amplifying regime turns dealers into aggressive sellers on any bounce attempts.\n\nBottom line: expect strong upward pressure as long as we stay above 6800, with potential acceleration above 6815.",
